      "content": "fair enough, i see what u mean about registers. but if we're talking about actual success in the real world, like getting a job or getting people to take ur ideas seriously in a professional setting, doesn't that mean text A is objectively \"better\"? if i'm a recruiter or a professor and i see text B, won't i automatically assume the person is less educated or less capable, even if they're actually genius? isnt the \"norm\" just a way to weed out people who don't fit a certain cultural mold?",
